easuring redshifts for three\nclasses of target objects: Emission Line Galaxies (ELGs) with $1.6<z<2.4$,\nLyman Break Galaxies (LBGs) with $2.4<z<4.0$, and quasars $2.1<z<3.5$. The ELGs\nand LBGs will be used as direct tracers of the underlying density field, while\nthe Lyman-$\\alpha$ forests in the quasar spectra will be utilized to probe\nstructure. Exposures of duration 1,800sec will guarantee a redshift\ndetermination efficiency of $90\\%$ for ELGS and at least $50\\%$ for LBGs. The\nsurvey will represent 100 nights per year for a 5-year MSE program. Finally,\nthree ideas for additional projects of cosmological interest are proposed.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 7 Mar 2019 20:07:36 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 21 Mar 2019 15:42:00 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-03-22"}
